<section id="about">
    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <p>
        Drawing upon 16 years of dedicated experience in education and skills project management, I possess a comprehensive skill set tailored to conceptualize, execute, and oversee a wide array of program endeavors. My academic background encompasses undergraduate and postgraduate qualifications from esteemed UK universities, complementing my professional journey which has primarily revolved around advancing education and skills within the development sector.
    </p>
    <p>
        Currently, I am leading various initiatives at the ILO, with a particular focus on enhancing the quality of Education and TVET/skills development systems in Bangladesh through the Skills 21 project funded by the European Union.
    </p>
</section>

<section id="experience">
    <h2>Experience</h2>
    <p>
        <strong>National Programme Officer (NQF & CSEs) - International Labour Organization (ILO) Skills 21</strong><br>
        July 2019 to Present
    </p>
    <p>
        Responsibilities:
        <ul>
            <li>Managing Skills complex projects including outcome-based planning, budgeting, and implementation.</li>
            <li>Collaborating closely with key stakeholders for seamless program execution.</li>
            <li>Organizing and providing input in discussions with National Steering Committee and technical committees.</li>
            <li>Reviewing and providing technical input on development of qualifications systems and quality assurance.</li>
            <li>Supporting vocational teacher training institutions to transform them into Centres of Skills Excellence (CSEs).</li>
            <li>Introducing and operationalizing gender planning and responsive action plans in skills development systems.</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
